definitions.definition: A person (originally a man) of authority in a Christian religious organization (a church).
examples: The bishop , a highly placed churchman , stated the religion's opinion.

definitions.definition: A member or adherent of an established church, especially the Church of England .

secondary_definitions: A person (originally a man) of authority in a Christian religious organization (a church). [from 16th c.]
A member or adherent of an established church, especially the Church of England . [from 17th c.]
